<div class="row g-4"><div class="col-12"><div class="Wrapper_wrapper__raXe4 Card_card__7rJy4 bg-body-secondary rounded-3 p-4 card position-relative ContentBlock_content__MOc3W" data-type="specPoint"><h2 id="locations-of-genes-on-a-chromosome">Locations of Genes on a Chromosome</h2><ul><li><p>Every <b>chromosome</b> consists of a long DNA molecule that contains several hundred or even thousands of <b>different genes </b>coding for different proteins</p><ul><li><p>A length of DNA that codes for a single polypeptide or protein is called a gene</p></li></ul></li><li><p>The position of a gene on a chromosome is known as its <b>locus</b> (plural: loci)</p><ul><li><p>Through experiments and genetic mapping techniques, scientists have been able to work out the <b>specific physical locations</b> of the genes on different chromosomes</p></li><li><p>Each gene occupies a <b>specific locus</b> so that the gene for a particular characteristic is always found at the <b>same position</b> on a particular chromosome</p></li></ul></li><li><p>Each gene can exist in two or more different forms called <b>alleles</b></p></li><li><p>Different alleles of a gene have slightly different nucleotide sequences but they still occupy the <b>same position</b> (locus) on the chromosome</p></li></ul><div class="mb-5" data-type="image"><img alt="Chromosomes showing gene and loci" class="ContentBlock_figure__6whpf" data-nimg="1" decoding="async" height="715" sizes="(max-width: 320px) 320w, (max-width: 640px) 640w, (max-width: 960px) 960w, (max-width: 1280px) 1280w, 1920w" src="Chromosomes-showing-gene-and-loci_1.png" srcset="https://cdn.savemyexams.com/cdn-cgi/image/f=auto,width=16/https://cdn.savemyexams.com/uploads/2021/03/Chromosomes-showing-gene-and-loci.png 16w, https://cdn.savemyexams.com/cdn-cgi/image/f=auto,width=32/https://cdn.savemyexams.com/uploads/2021/03/Chromosomes-showing-gene-and-loci.png 32w, https://cdn.savemyexams.com/cdn-cgi/image/f=auto,width=48/https://cdn.savemyexams.com/uploads/